<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="110" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,1730,1973]" pageId="20" pageNumber="110">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1803,1829]" pageId="20" pageNumber="110">Remarks</emphasis>
: This species was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Donnelly, T. W." box="[676,863,1803,1829]" pageId="20" pageNumber="110" pagination="52 - 90" refId="ref11774" refString="Donnelly, T. W. (1992) The Odonata of Central Panama and their position in the Neotropical odonate fauna, with a checklist, and descriptions of new species. In: Quintero, D. &amp; Aiello, A. (Eds.), Insects of Panama and Mesoamerica. Oxford University Press, New York, pp. 52 - 90." type="book chapter" year="1992">Donnelly (1992)</bibRefCitation>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[934,1026,1803,1829]" name="Panama" pageId="20" pageNumber="110">Panama</collectingCountry>
. Here, we report it for the first time from 
<collectingRegion box="[213,426,1839,1865]" country="Colombia" name="Choco" pageId="20" pageNumber="110">Chocó Department</collectingRegion>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[464,578,1839,1865]" name="Colombia" pageId="20" pageNumber="110">Colombia</collectingCountry>
. Males are small (abdomen close to 
<quantity box="[991,1066,1838,1865]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="20" pageNumber="110" unit="mm" value="35.0">35mm</quantity>
), and have distal abdominal segments (S7–S10) completely orange, cerci strongly curved in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[980,1080,1875,1901]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1940,1965]" captionTargetBox="[372,1216,930,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[363,1223,921,1921]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 11. Male cerci: H. peregrinum: Union Panamericana, Chocó (A) dorsal view (B) mediodorsal view (C) lateral view. Heteragrion tatama: PNN Tatamá, Risaralda (D) dorsal view (E) mediodorsal view (F) lateral view. Heteragrion valgum: Acandí, Chocó (G) dorsal view (H) mediodorsal view (I) lateral view. VbC: Ventro basal convexity." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253600/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="110">Fig. 11G</figureCitation>
) without ventrobasal convexity (
<figureCitation box="[160,261,1911,1937]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1940,1965]" captionTargetBox="[372,1216,930,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[363,1223,921,1921]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 11. Male cerci: H. peregrinum: Union Panamericana, Chocó (A) dorsal view (B) mediodorsal view (C) lateral view. Heteragrion tatama: PNN Tatamá, Risaralda (D) dorsal view (E) mediodorsal view (F) lateral view. Heteragrion valgum: Acandí, Chocó (G) dorsal view (H) mediodorsal view (I) lateral view. VbC: Ventro basal convexity." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253600/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="110">Fig. 11H</figureCitation>
) and with a distance between bifurcation of medial process and tip around one fourth the length of the cerci (
<figureCitation box="[220,317,1947,1973]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1940,1965]" captionTargetBox="[372,1216,930,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[363,1223,921,1921]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 11. Male cerci: H. peregrinum: Union Panamericana, Chocó (A) dorsal view (B) mediodorsal view (C) lateral view. Heteragrion tatama: PNN Tatamá, Risaralda (D) dorsal view (E) mediodorsal view (F) lateral view. Heteragrion valgum: Acandí, Chocó (G) dorsal view (H) mediodorsal view (I) lateral view. VbC: Ventro basal convexity." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253600/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="110">Fig 11G</figureCitation>
). We did not examine the female.
</paragraph>
